   <body>
      <context>
         <hazardstatement type="danger">
            <messagepanel>
               <typeofhazard>hazard of electric shock, explosion, or arc flash</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid>
                  <sl>
                     <sli>Electrical equipment must be installed, operated, serviced, and
maintained only by qualified personnel.</sli>
                     <sli>Apply appropriate personal protective equipment (PPE) and follow
safe electrical work practices.</sli>
                     <sli>Disconnection devices for AC and DC must be provided by others,
be readily accessible, and the function of the disconnection device
marked for its function.</sli>
                     <sli>Turn off all power supplying the UPS system before working on
or inside the equipment.</sli>
                     <sli>Before working on the UPS system, check for hazardous voltage
between all terminals including the protective earth.</sli>
                     <sli>The UPS contains an internal energy source. Hazardous voltage
can be present even when disconnected from the mains supply. Before
installing or servicing the UPS system, ensure that the units are
OFF and that mains and batteries are disconnected. Wait five minutes
before opening the UPS to allow the capacitors to discharge.</sli>
                     <sli>The UPS must be properly earthed/grounded and due to a high leakage
current, the earthing/grounding conductor must be connected first.</sli>
                  </sl>
               </howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <note>This procedure is only applicable
to 25–50 kVA systems.</note>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Loosen the ten screws and remove the indicated cover.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/replace_0j-0p2556_25-50kw_interfaceboard_removecover_w120mm_0000192345.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Note the location of the cables connected to the interface
board and disconnect the cables.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Loosen the four screws, one bolt and one nut, and slide
out the interface plate with the interface board.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/replace_0j-0p2560_25-50kw_sscboard_removeinterfaceass_w120mm_0000193416.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Note the location of the cables connected to the fan module
assembly board and disconnect the cables.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the fan module assembly board.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Note the location of the cables connected to the static
switch controller connection box and disconnect the cables.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Loosen the two screws and slide out the static switch controller
connection box.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/replace_0j-0p2560_25-50kw_sscboard_removesscconbox_w120mm_0000193414.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the static switch controller board.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/replace_0j-0p2560_25-50kw_sscboard_changesscboard_w120mm_0000193413.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Reverse the procedure for installation of the replacement
static switch controller board.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
